commit.message: Update version
Caddy is being ridiculous so I'll just change the URL
Check for error in case user cancels

Add unique URLs for registration 👨🏻‍💻

Fix #15
Fix table already exists error
Fix incorrect return type error

Change task scheduling implementation

The previous one did SQLite calls in a separate thread, which didn't work out.
Remove leftover import
Add missing scheduler start call
Add untested lockout implementation
Move function closer to caller

Add a security scheme

This brings us very close to finishing #7! The only thing needed now is a lockout period for repeated incorrect passwords.

IDs of several elements in the homepage's HTML have been changed to be clearer.
Add favicon
Factor out phone number validation
Remove useless line

Don't send users authorize link if already registered

Also, the app now checks is_possible_number() before calling format_number().

Fix #13 (finally!) 🎉

As a side effect, the search functions have been modified slightly. The phone number is passed in directly now, instead of being taken from the "words" list.

Clean up sql.py

With help from PyLint

Fix issue where it was possible for refresh_token to not be provided for a new account

This problem occurred during debugging but could have occurred when a user tried to register multiple phone numbers with the same Google account.

Replace blank pages with new site

Woohoo! Fixes #8.
Actually fix #10

Rename function

The function does not just get contacts. It gets them and then searches through them.
Fix #10
Fix warning: check: missing meta-data
Update version

Stop storing credential scopes

The scopes attribute was for informational purposes only. This fixes an unsupported object type error with SQLite when trying to add credentials.scopes to the database.
Add marker where phone number validation is needed

Add security configurations

Only send cookie over secure channels. Generated URLs now use HTTPS (so the user doesn't have to be redirected from HTTP to HTTPS).

Move function to match the user's flow

The user's flow from page to page aligns with the functions from top to bottom now

Fix "file_cache is unavailable when using oauth2client >= 4.0.0"

https://github.com/google/google-api-python-client/issues/299
